A critical challenge on proper functionality of the proposed structures is the impact of recombination. Although we have included the conventional loss mechanisms in the models, the effect of surface recombination was neglected. In the following, we separately investigate impact of this loss by adding a recombination rate on particles as well as the front side of the silicon layer in the structure A. Figure 11 shows the J–V plot of the cell assuming the dimensions and material properties listed in Table 1. The particles doping are assumed to be 1017cm-3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$10^{17} \,\mathrm{cm}^{-3}$$\end{document} and the silicon layer is assumed to have the doping 1017cm-3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$10^{17} \,\mathrm{cm}^{-3}$$\end{document}. As can be seen, by increasing the recombination velocity up to 103cms-1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$10^{3}\,\mathrm{cm\,s}^{-1}$$\end{document}, the J–V graph remains almost unchanged. At higher recombination velocities, both open circuit voltage and short circuit current are reduced. Due to that, the cell efficiency drops to 5.6% for the surface recombination velocity SRV=105cms-1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\mathrm{SRV} = 10^{5}\,\mathrm{cm\,s}^{-1}$$\end{document}. The graph shows that only at high surface recombination rates, efficiency is affected. This is because the carrier generation is mostly concentrated in the bulk of nanoparticles, away from the particle surface; the surface recombination is therefore effective on particle upper and lower areas where carrier transport happens.Figure 11
Impact of SRV on the J–V plot of the structure A. The dimensions and material properties of the cell are shown in Table 1.
